@startuml
title Elastic Resource Capacity Architecture - Mechanisms

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as CSC

cloud "Cloud Environment" as Cloud {

  component "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
  component "Intelligent\nAutomation Engine\n(scripts + workflow)" as IAE

  package "Virtualization Layer" as VL {
    component "Hypervisor" as HV
    component "VIM" as VIM
  }

  package "Virtual Server" as VS {
    component "Hosted Applications\nand IT Resources" as APP
  }

  package "Resource Pool" as RP {
    component "CPU Sub-pool" as CPUP
    component "RAM Sub-pool" as MEMP
  }

  package "Supporting Mechanisms" as Sup {
    component "Cloud Usage Monitor" as CUM
    component "Pay-Per-Use Monitor" as PPM
    component "Resource Replication" as RR
  }
}

CSC --> VS : requests
ASL --> VS : monitor
ASL --> IAE : signal
IAE --> HV : scaling request
IAE --> VIM : alternative path
VIM --> HV : delegates
HV --> CPUP : allocate / reclaim
HV --> MEMP : allocate / reclaim
CPUP --> VS : CPU added
MEMP --> VS : RAM added

CUM ..> VS : usage before/during/after\nscaling
PPM ..> VS : cost as elastic\nprovisioning fluctuates
RR ..> VS : new instances of\nscaled IT resources

note bottom of RP
  Vertical scaling: virtual server and its
  hosted applications are scaled in
  response to fluctuating processing
  requirements.
end note

@enduml

